11. exparte quarta: the Falcidian law of sc. 40 enacted that an heir should have at least a clear fourth of the estate, and that not more than three-fourtlrs should be left in legacies to others. If the natural heirs were disinherited for no sufficient reason, they could contest the will by an action called querela inofficiosi testamenti. This could be preveuted by leaving theru one-fourth of what they would have received if the testator had died intestate. Such a fourth was called the portio lepitima. Cf.
